### Spring Security Microservices API Testing
### Use this file to test the API endpoints

### 1. Register a new user
POST http://localhost:8080/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "password": "password123",
  "email": "test@example.com"
}

### 2. Login with credentials
POST http://localhost:8080/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 3. Validate JWT token (replace YOUR_TOKEN with actual token from login response)
POST http://localhost:8080/auth/validate?token=YOUR_TOKEN

### 4. Create user profile (replace YOUR_TOKEN with actual token)
POST http://localhost:8080/users
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "firstName": "Test",
  "lastName": "User",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "phoneNumber": "+1234567890",
  "address": "123 Main St",
  "city": "New York",
  "country": "USA",
  "bio": "This is a test user profile"
}

### 5. Get all users (replace YOUR_TOKEN with actual token)
GET http://localhost:8080/users
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN

### 6. Get user by ID (replace YOUR_TOKEN and ID with actual values)
GET http://localhost:8080/users/1
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN

### 7. Get user by username (replace YOUR_TOKEN and username with actual values)
GET http://localhost:8080/users/username/testuser
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN

### 8. Update user profile (replace YOUR_TOKEN and ID with actual values)
PUT http://localhost:8080/users/1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "firstName": "Updated",
  "lastName": "User",
  "email": "updated@example.com",
  "phoneNumber": "+1234567890",
  "address": "456 Updated St",
  "city": "Los Angeles",
  "country": "USA",
  "bio": "This is an updated test user profile"
}

### 9. Search users by name (replace YOUR_TOKEN with actual token)
GET http://localhost:8080/users/search?name=Test
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN

### 10. Get users by city (replace YOUR_TOKEN with actual token)
GET http://localhost:8080/users/city/New York
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN

### 11. Get users by country (replace YOUR_TOKEN with actual token)
GET http://localhost:8080/users/country/USA
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN

### 12. Deactivate user (replace YOUR_TOKEN and ID with actual values)
PUT http://localhost:8080/users/1/deactivate
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN

### 13. Delete user (replace YOUR_TOKEN and ID with actual values)
DELETE http://localhost:8080/users/1
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN

### 14. Test without authentication (should return 401)
GET http://localhost:8080/users

### 15. Test with invalid token (should return 401)
GET http://localhost:8080/users
Authorization: Bearer invalid_token
